Small and medium companies have to do it because larger customers - =
specifically banks - are requiring it. Part of that is regulatory and =
part of it is large orgs want to push risk and liability to the left and =
have the leverage to do so. Our addressable market is the supplier base =
for defense (100,000 companies and their subcontractors, which includes =
a lot of public companies and software vendors that do business with the =
military/intel community) and regulated industry (energy, telecom, =
healthcare, finance, critical manufacturing, transportation, smart =
cities, election infrastructure). There are hundreds of thousands of =
corporate entities who are regulated to care, and the mandates that kick =
in this year will be almost impossible to satisfy without automation. =
See: https://csrc.nist.gov/publications/detail/nistir/8276/draft =
<https://csrc.nist.gov/publications/detail/nistir/8276/draft> and =
